import { useEffect, useState } from "react" export default function List(){ const [userList , setUserList] = useState([]) const getUsers = ()=>{ fetch("http://localhost:5165/User/getUsers") .then(response=>response.json()) .then(response=>setUserList(response)) } const displayUsers= ()=>{ userList.map((user,key)=>{ return {user.id} {user.name} {user.email} {user.phone} }) } useEffect(()=>{ getUsers() },[]) return <>

List of Users

{displayUsers()}
Id Name Email Phone Action
}
